This article is a statement made by the President of the United States on the passing of Rick McKay. McKay was a veteran photojournalist who worked as the White House Photo Editor and dedicated his life to sharing the American Story through images. The President expresses his condolences to McKay's wife and children and praises McKay's kindness, humor, passion for NASCAR, love for his dog, and dedication to his job. The President thanks McKay for his contributions and says that his photos and stories will live on in history.